  "decision_conditions": [
    "FORMAL DECISION:  The appeal is allowed and planning permission granted insofar as it relates to the replacement roof enclosure, the new staircase and the refurbishment works including the rooflight to the shower room, but dismissed with regard to the proposed light shafts to Bedroom 2 at No. 18 Myddelton Square, London, EC1R 1YE in accordance with the terms of the Application No. P040078 dated 13th January 2004, and the plans submitted therewith including plan Nos. 053.400, 401, 402 and 501 subject to the following conditions:\r\n\r\n(1)  The development hereby permitted shall be begun before the expiration of five years from the date of this decision.\r\n\r\n(2)  That all new works and works of making good to the retained fabric internally or externally shall be finished to match the adjacent work with regard to the methods used, the materials, colour texture and profile.\r\n\r\n(3)  Before any works commence, details of the proposed staircase enclosure and glazing at a scale of 1:20 and 1:5 as appropriate shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.  The works shall then be implemented in accordance with the approved details."
